 having. Simply make it so that no mob below 30 is affected by TLC.  That's it.  Why would this work, in my opinion?  Because there really isn't much worth farming below level 30 anyway.  There are some quests that might be worth it for people to farm, but not that many.  Stricter enforcement of PnP, which I believe does say that you shouldn't be hunting well below your level, would help there.  I'm sorry, but it is ridiculous that Bako, a high-level Iksar monk, should have to be willing to trade a Wu's Fighting Stick, one of the better monk 1HBs, for an item that is the result of a quest that is really quite easy to do.  A saw that WTT ad and thought it was part silly, part sad.  Bako deserves to be able to do his epic, people!  OK, I'm sorry, I just think we have to ask VI to give us something here.  Many of us have invested large amounts of time in these characters, and the low server pop and TLC are making them so much less useful it isn't even funny.  If they won't help us out and the server population continues to go do down, do you think that they'll let us all /movelog to another one?  Not bloody likely. Very sorry to beat a dead, mutilated, sack of meat that doesn't even resemble a horse anymore after all the punishment it's taken, I just wanted opinions on this specific proposal.<br><br>Thanks<br> <p>Tenzin Dralha <BR>Human Monk <BR>30 Seasons Serving Quellious <BR>Proud Member of Starspun</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umheddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mheddik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 1:55:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm, good idea</span><hr size=1> I like it. It is simple, a