just a few hundred of their subscribers.  (In case you didn't know, a server is actually not just one machine, but many.  One computer can actually only support a few zones.  And though I don't know exactly what they use for servers, you can bet it ain't your grandma's Compaq) This hardly seems efficient, and one of the reasons they open new servers is to lighten the load on the other ones.  So not having people play on a server because it has severe problems doesn't even make sense for them financially.  They have an incentive to make people want to play here.  <br><br>Let's help VI make more money!  Let's lessen the bandwith strain on the other servers by getting people to play on Firiona Vie!  <br><br>Most of the rules, like the chat channel and grouping restrictions, work in my opinion.  TLC doesn't.  Let's tell VI this.  It's easy to fix.  Make a change in the code like my above proposal, or just take it out altogether.  Right now I'd say toss TLC and reinstate NO DROP.  Let's get this together, people.  The TLC monster is ruining the server I love. <p>Tenzin Dralha <BR>Human Monk <BR>30 Seasons Serving Quellious <BR>Proud Member of Starspun</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uprothall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prothall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 4:28:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pursue the level instead of the quest?</span><hr size=1> TLC was in place when the server went live back in October so everyone knew the ruleset of playing on this server. We all make choices and have consequences for our decisions. If you chose to outlevel mobs in the race to be high level and did not take the time to think about what you wanted out of your character quest wise, then I have no sympathy for anyone who feels they have been fouled by the TLC. <br><br>Even myself I have been hit by the TLC and its not a great feeling, but its not the end of the world not to get that item or piece of a quest you wanted. An idea is to ask someone who is perhaps lower in power then yourself to help complete a quest. Often times they will with the right incentive.<br><br>Simple solution to this issue really, either focus on the high end mobs and keep leveling your hearts out, or perhaps slow down and do some research on existing quests you want to complete.  Another idea is to go to a standard blue server where you can compete with level 50+ people farming items 20 levels below them. Nothing is perfect, not even Firona Vie, but Im here because of the TLC and other aspects such as /auc /ooc and the alignment based grouping. <br><br>[ANONYMOUS] is making things tough to find groups for most people, this is something that i would like to see changed to improve everyones grouping chances. This is why I feel  part of the reason why there was a mass exodus from this server once people started getting out of the untwinked &quot;soloing&quot; levels.<br><br>Best wishes!<br> <p><BR><center><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~abspara/Valanissigpic.jpg" height=90 width=350 </center></a><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uprothall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Prothall</A> at: 12/30/01 4:53:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 5:13:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.