ds are people who are brand new to the game, and that's a good thing.<br><br>So, my vote:  Napster bad.  TLC good.<br><br>I'm wearing Sarhea's thong. <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>Taruun of Shar Val<BR><BR>Master Cook <BR>Lousy Fletcher<BR>Grandmaster Lech<BR><I>"Show me a good mouser and I'll show you a cat with bad breath" -- Garfield</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 11:01:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin quests...</span><hr size=1> Most of us agree some form of TLC is good. Just that the current form of TLC isn't working.<br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 12/30/01 11:48:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 241<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 11:14:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin quests...</span><hr size=1> I haven't seen where it's not working.  As far as I've seen, it's working exactly the way it was supposed to.<br><br>A note on the Shammy epic thread... I posted that to find out if TLC was blocking it, so that we could determine if the quest was broken and get it fixed early.  That's why I asked FnF to kill the broodling to be sure. <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>Taruun of Shar Val<BR><BR>Master Cook <BR>Lousy Fletcher<BR>Grandmaster Lech<BR><I>"Show me a good mouser and I'll show you a cat with bad breath" -- Garfield</I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 11:52:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin quests...</span><hr size=1> Gotcha. I wasnt sure either. The other quests should be the proof you need though no?<br><br>The Ethreal Weapon Quests and the newbie quests? Its in my post above on this thread if ya want to read it.<br><br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A> at: 12/30/01 11:53:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/31/01 12:43:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=986.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Luclin quests...</span><hr size=1> Hrmmm... the longsword and hammer quests appear to be based on the same assumption as the Vah Shir and Sonic Wolf quests:  that they'd be completed by Vah Shir.  That being said, if they're useable by other races, then on another server you would simply need to run the quest and get the result.  No need to interact with anyone other than the required NPC's.<br><br>This is FV, however, so the rules change slightly.  You need to RP through it.  I'm not familiar with the quests, but if TLC is keeping you from completing it, then the answer is to ally yourself with Vah Shir of the appropriate level, and assist them as they assist you.  That way you can complete the quest.<br><br>Let's not forget, Verant puts new quests into the game quite often.  This is not a static environment.  Therefore, on a TLC server, if you want to run a quest that is newly introduced and you're above the level where you can actually run it, you need to ally yourself with others.  This stops quests from being dominated by high level players as soon as they're introduced.  I'm not saying that this would happen on FV, but it does make sense to me.<br><br>For my part, I'd be glad to help you out with these quests.  It gives me something to look forward to, and I kind of look at it the same way as when I help out someone lower than me... I get nothing for it, but you'll remember me as a good guy in the future.  Maybe you'll even buy some of my fish rolls.  Not holding my breath though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>So, again, my response is that FV breeds an intelligent player.  And because of this, we can work around TLC through interaction, which is why it was implemented.<br><br>Just my two coppers. <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>Taruun of Shar Val<BR><BR>Master Cook <BR>Lousy Fletcher<BR>Grandmaster Lech<BR><I>"Show me a good mouser and I'll show you a cat with bad breath" -- Garfield</I